            <h2><a name="summaries" id="summaries"></a>Quick Reference Summaries to Facilitate Training</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="http://www.aap.org/en-us/advocacy-and-policy/federal-advocacy/Documents/ACAImplementationFactSheets.pdf">AAP Health Reform Implementation fact sheets and resources</a> (2013) consists of a packet of one-page fact sheets on ACA implementation specifically focused on MCH. (American Academy of Pediatrics (AAP)).</li>
              <li><a href="http://www.hhs.gov/healthcare/rights/index.html">About the Law</a> and <a href="http://www.hhs.gov/healthcare/rights/law/index.html">Read the Law</a> (2013) present section-by-section outlines of the law and links to the legislation. (Health Insurance Marketplace, HealthCare, U.S. Department of Health and Human Services).
              </li>
              <li><a href="http://www.amchp.org/Policy-Advocacy/health-reform/resources/Documents/OutreachandEnrollmentFinal.pdf">The Affordable Care Act: Outreach and Enrollment</a> (2013) includes suggested steps for MCH Leaders to support outreach and ACA enrollment. (AMCHP).</li>
              <li><a href="http://www.epi.umn.edu/mch/factsheets">Factsheets About the Affordable Care Act and MCH Populations</a> (2012-2013)  provide ACA provisions and implications for specific populations. (Center for Leadership Education in Maternal and Child Public Health at the University of Minnesota).</li>
              <li><a href="http://www.hhs.gov/healthcare/facts/bystate/statebystate.html">State by State Interactive Map</a> (continually updated) describes state efforts related to the ACA.  (U.S. Department of Health and Human Services).<br />
              </li>
              <li><a href="http://kaiserfamilyfoundation.files.wordpress.com/2011/04/8061-021.pdf">Summary of the Affordable Care Act</a> (2013) provides a summary of the law and changes made to the law by subsequent legislation. It focuses on provisions to expand coverage, control health care costs, and improve health care delivery system. (Henry J. Family Kaiser Foundation).</li>
            </ul>
            <hr />
            <h2><a name="tools" id="tools"></a>Tools to Augment Training</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="http://www.commonwealthfund.org/Maps-and-Data/State-Exchange-Map.aspx">State Action to Establish Health Insurance Marketplaces</a> presents an interactive map that can be used to review the status of state action on state health insurance&nbsp;marketplaces or exchanges,&nbsp;and&nbsp;view key aspects&nbsp;of state-run marketplaces. (Commonwealth Fund).</li>
              <li><a href="http://laborcenter.berkeley.edu/pdf/2012/health_reform_summary12.pdf">Summary of Affordable Care Act Provisions Affecting Children, Non-Elderly Adults and Employers</a> (2012) provides information about Medicaid/CHIP eligibility, exchanges, premium subsidies, cost sharing, health plan standards, and taxes and credits. (University of California, Berkeley Labor Center).</li>
              <li><a href="http://kff.org/interactive/zooming-in-health-reform-medicaid-uninsured-local-level">Zooming in on Health Reform:  Understanding the Potential Impact of the ACA on Medicaid and the Uninsured at the Local Level</a> (2013) present interactive maps that allow users to zoom in on their state and see how the number and composition of individuals enrolled in Medicaid or without insurance coverage could change if the state expands Medicaid. (Kaiser Commission on Medicaid and the Uninsured).</li>
            </ul>
            <hr />
            <h2><a name="additional" id="additional"></a>Additional ACA Resources</h2>
            <ul>
              <li><img src="../images/MCHDevCtr-Trans-Stat.gif" alt="MCH Workforce Development Center" width="313" height="140" border="0" class="right border" /><a href="http://www.amchp.org/Transformation-Station/Pages/Home.aspx">The National MCH Workforce Development Center</a> at UNC Chapel Hill, in cooperation with the Maternal and Child Health Bureau (MCHB), and in partnership with the Association of Maternal and Child Health Programs (AMCHP) and national experts in MCH innovation and quality improvement,  offers state and territorial Title V leaders training, collaborative learning, coaching and consultation in implementing health reform using a variety of learning platforms. The Transformation Station, hosted within the AMCHP website, contains information and resources related to the Center's four cores: access to care, quality improvement, systems integration, and change management.
                <ul>
                  <li><a href="http://www.amchp.org/Transformation-Station/Pages/ACA-101.aspx">The Affordable Care Act: A Working Guide for MCH Professionals</a> provides  an overview of major provisions in the ACA with a focus on implications for MCH populations. </li>
                  <li><a href="http://ghpc.gsu.edu/files/2015/02/MCHPlanningToolWorkbook_web.pdf">Leading through Health System Change: A Public Health Opportunity</a> helps to develop the competencies required of contemporary public health leaders to implement the Affordable Care Act (ACA) and other health system transformations. <a href="http://www.acaplanningtool.com/home">Online version of the tool</a>.</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li><a href="https://www.mchlibrary.org/professionals/aca.php">Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act: Resources for Professionals</a> and <a href="https://www.mchlibrary.org/families/frb-ACA.php">Resources for Families</a> (2013) present  resources about the ACA's major provisions, policy developments, and implementation efforts. (Florida MCH Training projects and the National Center for Education in Maternal and Child Health).</li>
            </ul>
